GTX Corp said Nippon Steel Co of Japan,in a move to diversify into high technology, invested eight mlndlrs in GTX.    Nippon's move was the result of current exchange rates andthe revaluation of the yen, which "have made the U.S.electronics industry an attractive investment opportunity forJapanese corporations," according to a GTX statement.    GTX noted that Nippon is expecting sales of 27 billion dlrsby 1995. Of that amount, six billion dlrs is targeted forelectronics. GTX, located in Phoenix, makes computerizedsystems that read drawings and transfer them into data bases. Reuter&#3;